{
  "texts": [
    "Among them, 1,282 genes overlapped in both comparisons (Additional file 1: Table S8; Additional file 2: Fig.",
    "The remaining 1,627 (56% of the candidate genes) in HW-SL and 1,511 (54%) in HW-NL represent those with divergent histories since the origin of domesticated Tartary buckwheat.",
    "Only 330 genes located in 44 selective sweeps in HW-SL comparison and 317 genes located in 78 selective sweeps in HW-NL comparison were overlapped with previous study.",
    "This was because more than half of HW accessions and 10% of the NL accessions were newly added in this study.",
    "In addition, de-correlated composite of multiple signals (DCMS) approach was also used to identify selective sweeps."
  ]
}